# VidyaBot — Multilingual AI Tutor for Rural India

## Project Context
React Native + Expo SDK 55 app for offline STEM education in rural India.
Target devices: Android with 512MB to 2GB RAM, zero reliable internet.
All AI inference runs ON-DEVICE using llama.cpp via Android JNI bridge.
22 Indian scheduled languages supported with full offline ASR and TTS.

## Critical Constraints
- NEVER assume internet connectivity for any core feature
- All AI inference must be async and non-blocking using queues
- Memory budget: UI layer max 80MB, AI engine max 400MB, total max 512MB
- Battery: throttle all inference when battery is below 20 percent
- Use SQLite via expo-sqlite for ALL persistent storage, never AsyncStorage for curriculum data
- Every user-facing string must use i18n translation keys, never hardcode English text
- Offline scenario must always be handled first, online scenario second

## Technology Stack
- React Native 0.76 with Expo SDK 55
- TypeScript in strict mode always
- Zustand for all global state management
- React Navigation 6 for all navigation
- llama.cpp GGUF models via custom Android JNI native module
- Whisper.cpp for speech recognition via native module
- VITS and MMS models for text to speech via native module
- expo-sqlite for all database needs
- MediaPipe for all computer vision features
- expo-camera for camera access

## Code Style Rules
- Functional components only, never class components
- Every component must handle loading state and error state
- Prefer composition over deep prop drilling
- Write JSDoc comments on every exported function
- Always handle offline case first, then online case
- Use React.memo on all list item components
